question.en:
In Nest.js, what is the primary difference between a Guard and an Interceptor?
typescript
// Guard
@Injectable()
export class AuthGuard implements CanActivate {
  canActivate(context: ExecutionContext): boolean {
    return true;
  }
}

// Interceptor
@Injectable()
export class LoggingInterceptor implements NestInterceptor {
  intercept(context: ExecutionContext, next: CallHandler) {
    return next.handle();
  }
}

Which statement best describes their roles?

